title: Value and Good Service
text: I would recommend Travellers Autobarn for the value and services that they have shown to me during my trip recently. It was a smooth transition from picking up until I returned the van to them. Both Molly and Sam were accommodating and helpful during the transition. I am a value sensitive person and looking for a good service of the campervan industry. The campervan that was allocated to me was fantastic and hassle free throughout my journey. Thank you Travellers Autobarn!

title: Peace and quiet
text: I passed this place while I was staying in Emu Park and do happened that this place is known to all the travellers. This is the iconic symbol of the Emu Park and favourite area for locals to do their morning activities. It is very quiet and if you want to free you negativity of your life and connect your soul to Mother nature, this is one of the place.

title: Easy and accommodating
text: Staff are very friendly and helpful. I booked a day before I arrived and managed to accommodate me a spot near the beach front. On the day I arrived I also asked to stay for another day and they managed to accommodate me for a another spot near the beach area. Toilet and shower areas are cleaned with sanitation ready.

title: Central and convenience
text: I stayed with Sappho house for almost a week when visiting Athens and the Greek Islands. The owner is so helpful and accommodating to our needs. He manages to look after one luggage while we are away to the Greek Islands. Room is clean and tidy. You have shared kitchen and bathroom. The location is the near to supermarkets and restaurants

title: Remembering the past
text: Well preserved heritage by far. Imagined that these ruins of House of Apollo, the sanctuary of Athena were built by hands.

title: Beautiful views and awesome Mediterranean foods
text: I got Mossouka for my lunch. The food was delicious and not bad for a price. And you will be amused by a wonderful view of hills and mountains. Staff were friendly too!

title: Awesome place to visit
text: As a holiday goers and occasionally travel in Europe. Acropolis is must to visit. Until now I am still wondering how they build the pillars and walls during that time without modern equipment.

title: Holiday
text:
I loved the food. The staff are friendly and efficient. Recommended for tourists to try there food.
Somemore, its a family owned restaurant so you can't get wrong with it.

title: Island hopping
text:
We managed to take a 2 day and 1 night tour package. The package includes all meals and drinks for the entire island hopping tour and 5 islands to visit.

Stuff was very friendly and assisted us. Islands are very beautiful and reserved. You felt that you are being in the 'Castaway' movie. One of the island has long sandbar that you will enjoy the beauty. Antonia island is my favourite of all the islands.

If you have the chance visit the Islas de Gigantes before it will be touristy and crowded so you'll enjoy the serenity and tranquility of the islands.

title: Scenic from the top
text: If you are visiting Miyajima, on my own experience. I would suggest that you better be with cable car up to Mount Misen first. You can see all the fabulous views up the top of the cable car station. Is 100 percent you'll love it.

title: Miyajima heritage
text: If you interested in the history of Japan. This place is full of heritage. From the ancient street to the shrine and temple. Some domesticated deers are on the park to amused you.

title: Awesome
text: Itsukushima shrine will amused you of history behind it. When I was there I think of the past of Japan. The hardwork and resourcefulness of the Japanese people. They preserved everything!

title: Easy ride across the straight
text: Fantastic ride across the straight. No hassle if you have JR rail pass. There are two ferry services one of the JR and other with the private company.

title: Awesome views
text: From the cable car station, you have to be prepared to climb on foot towards Mount Misen. You need to have water with you and you need to stop if you need to rest. Remember that its steep hiking track so better reserved your strength. Once you are there you will reward yourself with awesome views. A 360 degrees view!

title: Preservation of great destruction
text: Ruins left by first atomic bomb. you can see from the ruins how powerful is the bomb that destroy the city of Hiroshima. A lesson for us that A bomb could wipe out the human race.

title: Osaka great heritage
text: Osaka Castle is located right in middle of Osaka's loop train services. So you it's a good thing to visit the Osaka famous heritage.

title: Theme park Osaka
text: Easy to get access to this theme park. A lots of restaurants to choose if feel hungry. Walk towards the Universal studios will amused you of scenery.

title: Great Osaka Heritage
text: Impressive preserved of the past. If you visited Osaka in future, please have a visit in the most popular site the Osaka Castle. A lot of walks and food stalls. And the best of all is that I eaten the most sweetest strawberries.

title: Relaxing near river
text: Christchurch is excellent choice to relax around Victoria Square. It is not a crowded and big compare to other cities.

title: Summer fun at the beach
text: Taylors mistake is popular of Christchurch resident during summer. Ideally, if you wanted to enjoy the sea breeze and cool you down.
place: Taylors Mistake - Awaroa / Godley Head Walk

title: Great Negros Island Heritage
text: If you are visiting Bacolod City in Philippines. It is a must to visit the greatest heritage park of Talisay City. There is entrance fee to get in to this heritage park but it is worth to see the old ruin building. There is a tour guide to show you around and served you with smile. One of the tour guide, he will crack a joke every time so doesn't turned out to be boring. Have a visit and you will amused with it.

title: Lighthouse in the Great Ocean Road
text: If you wanted to tour the Great Ocean Road of Victoria. It is better to visit this place to relax for couple of hours from driving. Spectacular view from the the foot of the Split Point Lighthouse.

title: Cafe at the Split Point Lighthouse
text: After amused by the spectacular view at the lookout. It might be better to have a coffee break before touring at the Great Ocean Road. Good and fast cafe' service.

title: Touring Great Ocean Road
text: Great Ocean Road has a lot of spectacular views throughout my journey from Melbourne to Portland. All the way, I stopped in Torquay, Anglesea, Aireys Inlet, Lorne, Apollo Bay ( lunch - best to stop), Princetown, Port Campbell (12 Apostles, the Arch, Bay of Martyr etc) and overnight at Portland.

title: Water Falls and Summit Lookout
text:
Grampians National Park is a lot to explore and a day is not enough. Considering the Mackenzie Falls, I would love to spend a minimum of 3 hours there of amazing views of the falls. Easy to medium trekking experience required to see at the foot of the falls. Need a water if required.
The Balconies lookout is most amazing views up at the summit.

title: Wow .... views
text: The Balconies is the most amazing view at the summit. 360 degrees views at the fire station lookout. You will loved this lookout, believed me

title: Half Day walking
text: Godley head is good if you loved to do some walking for half day. You can passed in a treacherous walking trail but you loved the views. Its a 3 hours walk the whole journey.

title: Nice ride to the top
text: Gondola is the fastest way to reach the top of the Godley Head. You can see the entire Christchurch. There is a good cafe shop at the summit.

title: Overlooking Brisbane
text: We droved towards Mount Cootha lookout. It was very spectacular view of Greater Brisbane from lookout. Cafe right at top and added more fun and refreshing moments while watching the view up above. Recommended for both kids and adults, must see while visiting the city.

title: Sydney Habour view
text: Getting to harbour area by train is easiest and convenient way. There are many things to do at the Sydney harbour. We managed to watch a street entertainment that was amusing. We walked to at the towards the famous Sydney Opera House and have a spectacular view of the Sydney Bridge. Few harbour bar along the way. Dropping a beer that added more spectacular moments.Great views and moments so if you visiting Sydney have a go.

title: Spectacular views of Blue Mountains
text: Catching a train from Sydney Central is awesome experience and convenient way to Katoomba station. From there you can able to choose a explore bus or council bus service to Echo Point. Once there you will definitely enjoy the spectacular view of Three Sisters. Amazing nature made through time. A good walk to Scenic world with more impressive falls and gorges. I loved my experiences with Blue mountains view and highly recommended it for tourists visiting Sydney.

title: Submerged glass tunnel
text: It was part of the 4 attractions package. The whole visit includes the Madame Tussuads, wild life, Sydney Tower. Good deal for all these attractions. Two submerged glass tunnel you need to pass which will amused you. Before you reached the submerged glass tunnel, there are many other underwater species exhibits that enlighten your knowledge. I also admitted that never encounter some species in my entire life and is worth paying a visit with your children. Highly recommended for kids and adult.

title: Awesome Sydney View
text: Sydney is located at the heart of the Sydney Central Business District. Is a must if you're visiting. You can view the entire city in 360 degrees from the tower. You will enjoy the spectacular view of the skyscraper and the harbor. Important is to bring a camera with you so you don't missed it. At the bottom of the tower, Westfield shopping center to enjoy further your holiday.
